at U.S. forces will act on several fronts, including intelligence-gathering and counter-insurgency operations. Already, U.S. forces have begun dropping two sets of pamphlets, one stating, \"One of our American guests is missing. Return the guest to his home.\" and the other, \"If you do not release the U.S. soldier then [...] you will be hunted.\" The mayor of Ketchum has said that, \"As the mayor, I can say this is a community situation. [...] I trust the leadership of this country, the wisdom of the people who are serving and the decisions that led up to the situation.\""}
